Vectors comparisons

Source: R/vectors_comparisons.R
vectors_comparisons.Rd

Identify similarities and differences between two R vectors.

vectors_comparisons(first_vector, second_vector, comparison_type, output)

Arguments

first_vector

vector expected.
second_vector

vector expected.
comparison_type

character expected. Type of comparison expected, you can choose between "difference" or "equality". "Difference" highlight element(s) of the first vector not present in the second, and "equality" check if two vectors are exactly the same.
output

character expected. Kind of expected output. You can choose between "message", "report" or "logical".

Examples

vectors_comparisons(first_vector = c(1, 2, 3, 5),
                    second_vector = c(1, 2, 4, 3),
                    comparison_type = "difference",
                    output = "report")
#> # A tibble: 4 × 2
#>   first_vector vectors_comparisons_output           
#>          <dbl> <chr>                                
#> 1            1 no difference                        
#> 2            2 no difference                        
#> 3            3 no difference                        
#> 4            5 data not present in the second sector
